">
'''Level 122''', '''also known as “The Indoor American Dream”, is described as a massive complex of enclosed indoor neighbourhoods designed to resemble idealized American suburban environments. The level is divided into several distinct sections, each connected through houses, pathways, hidden exits, or uncommon transitions between areas. Artificial skies, controlled lighting, and abnormal architecture are present throughout the level.'''
<div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Level 122.thing (1).png|450x600px|center|link]]<br>'''A Well Kept Residence'''<br><br></div>

'''Upon entering Level 122, wanderers will typically appear inside the garden of a suburban residence. Placed somewhere nearby, usually on a patio table, garden chair, or small outdoor shelf, will be a single house key. Wanderers are strongly advised to take this key, as it appears to be the only key connected to their assigned residence.'''

'''If the key is lost, stolen, or abandoned, regaining access to the residence becomes extremely difficult. No duplicate keys have been documented, and locked doors rarely reopen without the original key.'''

'''The most common section of Level 122 consists of large suburban houses enclosed within enormous concrete chambers. These chambers are constructed from smooth concrete walls and ceilings painted with artificial skies, clouds, and atmospheric effects intended to imitate an outdoor environment. The illusion is convincing from a distance, though closer inspection reveals imperfections within the painted clouds and lighting.'''

'''The houses themselves resemble upper middle class American homes, mainly styled after suburban architecture from the late 1990s to early 2010s. Interiors are usually fully furnished, containing living rooms, kitchens, bedrooms, garages, and backyard areas. Most houses appear clean and maintained despite showing no signs of occupants. The outdoor sections surrounding these homes are also located indoors, consisting of artificial grass, decorative plants, patios, and fenced yards beneath the false sky.'''

'''If a wanderer manages to locate a exit within one of these houses, they may enter another section of Level 122. This could also lead to other houses.'''

==Locations==
<tabber>
Residence Hallways=



{{Blurimage|file=Level 122.3.png|caption=“A picture showing a residence hallway”}}
'''The Neighbourhood is a secondary area of Level 122 consisting of long indoor residential streets lined with closely packed suburban houses. Unlike the larger residential chambers, this area is narrower and more enclosed, with rows of houses positioned side by side beneath a massive artificial ceiling painted to resemble a bright sky. Decorative pathways, artificial grass, porches, and rocking chairs are common throughout the area.'''

'''The environmental conditions within the Neighbourhood fluctuate noticeably. Temperatures can shift from slightly cold to somewhat hot over short periods of time, usually ranging between 12°C (53.6°F) and 29°C (84.2°F). These changes happen without warning, and different parts of the area may feel warmer or colder than others.'''

'''The ceiling above the Neighbourhood is made of large illuminated panels displaying artificial skies and clouds. While most remain functional, some panels are damaged or have partially fallen down. It also the only light source expect for lamps inside the houses. Broken panels may be found on pathways or between houses, occasionally exposing unfinished concrete above the false sky.'''

'''Most houses within the Neighbourhood are locked. However, many of them show signs of activity inside. Wanderers commonly report hearing muffled conversations, footsteps, televisions, running water, or objects being moved from within the homes. In some cases, shadows may briefly pass behind windows or curtains. The only confirmed residents of this section are [[Facelings]], which rarely leave their houses. [[Facelings]] usually act like normal neighbours and may greet wanderers if encountered outside. They are generally friendly, however, wanderers shouldn't enter their homes, even if invited inside. If a [[Facelings]] does leave its house, it is usually heading toward the Shopping Experience to buy supplies or other items before returning home.'''

|-|

Shopping Experience=


{{Blurimage|file=Level 122.4.png|caption=“A picture showing the Shopping Experience”}}
'''The Shopping Experience is a lesser-known section of Level 122. The Shopping Experience is a large enclosed street featuring a wide variety of shops and stores along both sides of the street. The walls have a Western European-style appearance, with most buildings being shades of orange or pale yellow. The street is mostly made of orange bricks, which have a strange and somewhat unusual design. Above the stores is a painted blue sky that emits a bright white light. Located in the center of the street are there streetlights, which are the only other structures present. The streetlights are also the only other light source inside the area besides the roof lamps. No benches or toilets have been found within the area.'''

'''Stores are present on both sides of the street, though most appear closed or abandoned. The interiors vary from store to store, but all share some type of recognizable layout. Inside the shops are various items, ranging from snacks to unusual surprises. There is a large variety of stores, ranging from grocery stores to laundromats.'''

</tabber>
