==Environment==
<div style="
font-family:Cinzel, serif;
margin:1em;
font-size:17px;
text-align:center;

color:#BFDFFF;
text-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(180,220,255,0.45);
line-height:1.8;
letter-spacing:0.6px;
">
'''Level 122 has unstable environmental conditions which gradually become more noticeable the longer a wanderer remains inside the level. Temperatures fluctuate unpredictably, often swinging between unusually cold and uncomfortably hot conditions over short periods of time. These changes can be severe, with indoor and outdoor sections sometimes having completely different temperatures.'''

'''This level is also affected by [[Phenomenon 15]].'''

'''The residential sections of Level 122 appear to discourage prolonged stays. The longer a wanderer remains inside a house, the higher the chance that the electrical systems will begin failing. Lights may flicker, appliances may shut down, and eventually the power can fail entirely. In most cases, this forces wanderers to leave the building and return outside. Houses affected by power loss often become darker, quieter, and noticeably colder or warmer depending on the current environmental conditions.'''

'''The Shopping Experience also appears to change over time. The longer a wanderer remains in Level 122, the more shops seem to become open and accessible. Previously abandoned storefronts may unlock, interior lights may activate, and new stores may appear to begin operating. The reason for this behavior is unknown.'''

==Entities & Dangers==
<div style="
font-family:Cinzel, serif;
margin:1em;
font-size:17px;
text-align:center;

color:#BFDFFF;
text-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(180,220,255,0.45);
line-height:1.8;
letter-spacing:0.6px;
">
'''The only known entities present within Level 122 are [[Facelings]]. They are generally friendly and often behave like ordinary neighbours or shoppers. However, wanderers are strongly advised to never enter their houses, even if invited inside.'''

'''If a wanderer enters a Faceling’s house, they should attempt to leave as soon as possible. After prolonged time inside, the Faceling’s behavior may begin to change noticeably. Their personality often becomes increasingly unstable, and they may become irritated or aggressive over minor actions or simple conversation.'''

'''In hostile situations, Facelings have been observed attacking wanderers with household objects, most commonly kitchen knives. They will often retrieve a weapon from the kitchen before charging at the wanderer. Due to the confined layouts of most houses, escaping these encounters can be difficult.'''

==Colonies & Outposts==
'''Due to [[Phenomenon 15]], no colonies or outposts have ever been successfully established within Level 122.'''

==<span style="font-size:30px;">Addendum</span>==
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Discovery Log: "Level 122"</span><br>
During exploration of Level 122, multiple wanderers reported discovering a single key shortly after entering the level. The key was typically found placed somewhere within the garden area of a suburban residence, often on a table, chair, or near the front entrance.

Testing confirmed that the key only functions on one specific house, believed to be the wanderer’s assigned residence. Attempts to use the key on neighboring houses consistently failed.

In one documented case, a wanderer lost their key inside The Shopping Experience. After returning to their residence, the front door remained locked, and no alternative method of entry was successful. No replacement keys or duplicate copies have been discovered.

</div></span>

==Entrances & Exits==
===Entrances===
*'''Noclipping through a metal door on [[Level 19]] may lead here.
*'''Noclipping through a tree on [[Level 553]] may lead here.
*'''Entering any western European style house have a small chance to lead here.
*'''Touching a streetlamp on [[Level 829]] will lead here.
===Exits===
*'''Finding a old poster and touching will lead to [[Level 123]].
*'''Destroying a beige wall in any house will lead to [[Level 193]].
*'''Finding a book with the title ''827'' will lead to [[Level 827]].

